Agent Capability Contract (ACC)

ACC is an open specification for Agent-to-Business capability declaration.

ACC was initially proposed by the BailingHub project and is maintained as an implementation-neutral open contract.

Truthful compatibility statements such as "implements the ACC v1 Runtime Profile" are allowed.

Do not imply official ACC certification or maintainer endorsement unless explicitly granted.

No product implementation defines ACC semantics or receives privileged compatibility or registry status.
